title: Sidewall, "Maidens and a Victory", 1810–15
description: On pale green ground, dotted with darker green, two isolated scenes of two maidens in classical costume and Amor. Between the two scenes, a winged Victory and scrolls in yellow. Band of floral and bead runs along the right side.

exhibitions.title: The Cooper-Hewitt Collections: A Design Resource
